2. **`exit_thread_with_allocator`**: This function cleans up the thread-local storage allocator for the current thread by calling `allocator.exit_thread()`. This releases any thread-specific resources and ensures proper cleanup before the thread terminates.

These functions provide a clean interface for managing the lifecycle of TLS allocators across different threads, ensuring proper initialization and cleanup of thread-local resources.

