2. **`conditional_clear_buffer`**: This function calls `buffer.conditional_clear()`, which only clears the buffer when the read pointer and write pointer are at the same position (meaning all data has been read). This is useful for optimizing buffer reuse by resetting it only when it's been fully consumed.

